   title = {Topological recognition of critical transitions in time series of cryptocurrencies},
   journal = {Physica A: Statistical Mechanics and its Applications},
   volume = {548},
   pages = {123843},
   abstract = {We analyze four major cryptocurrencies (Bitcoin, Ethereum, Litecoin, and Ripple) before the digital asset market crash at the beginning of 2018. We also analyze Bitcoin before some of the mini-crashes that occurred during the period 2016–2018. All relevant time series exhibited a highly erratic behavior. We introduce a methodology that combines topological data analysis with a machine learning technique – k-means clustering – in order to characterize the emerging chaotic regime in a complex system approaching a critical transition. We first test our methodology on the complex system dynamics of a Lorenz-type attractor. Then we apply it to the four major cryptocurrencies. We find early warning signals for critical transitions, i.e., crashes, in the cryptocurrency markets.},
